[[ch01-tokens]]
== Chapter 1: Tokens — Text to Numbers

____
_"Before a model can think about words, it must forget that words exist."_
____

A language model does not read text.
It reads *integers*.
The first job of any GPT pipeline is to convert a string of characters into a sequence of integers.
That conversion is called *tokenization*, and the integers it produces are called *token IDs*.

This chapter explains what tokens are, how they are produced, and what they look like as data structures.
We implement a tiny byte-pair encoding tokenizer in Scheme.

